article.description: Alanna Smith tallied 20 points and Kaylee Johnson added 10 points and 15 rebounds to propel Stanford to a 70-57 victory over Washington State on Friday night.
article.headline: Stanford women beat Washington State for 63rd straight time
article.linkText: Stanford women beat Washington State for 63rd straight time
article.story:
PULLMAN, Wash. --  The women's basketball game between No. 16 Stanford and Washington State scheduled for Sunday was cancelled after the sudden passing of the Cougars' director of strength and conditioning David Lang.

Lang, a longtime member of the athletics department, worked directly with the women's basketball and men's and women's golf programs.

Stanford (20-9, 14-3) entered the day a game behind No. 8 Oregon for the Pac-12 Conference championship. The Ducks played at Arizona, which is 11th in the conference, on Sunday.

Washington State (10-19, 3-14) is locked into the No. 10 seed for the Pac-12 Tournament, which begins on Wednesday.
